subsection.p:
Compute the two local terms: \rho_t=-1, and
\nabla\cdot\mathbf J = \frac{\partial x}{\partial x} + \frac{\partial 0}{\partial y} + \frac{\partial 0}{\partial z} = 1.
So \boxed{\rho_t+\nabla\cdot\mathbf J=0.}

This suggests the general local law:
\boxed{\rho_t+\nabla\cdot\mathbf J=s.}
When there is no source,
\boxed{\rho_t+\nabla\cdot\mathbf J=0.}

